@The Ram - realize we're not trying to be stubborn here, it's simply that there are no identifying markings on your strings to tell us what kind they are. And like Gorn says, ancient strings are just ancient strings. Nothing new will feel or sound the same, even if you were able to determine the brand. It's sort of like asking what kind of motor oil your used car originally came with. Only the people who built it would have any idea.
What you *can* go on are the size of the string (the 'gauge', how thick they are), the type of windings (look like rounds), and then what kind of music you want to play - because that will steer you to something currently in production that might suit you. People are suggesting things like flats and pressurewounds because we assume you like the 'deadness' (more thump, less zing) of the strings being old.
Also, the mention of the strings being out of tune is an odd one. Do you mean you can't tune the bass and have it stay in tune for any length of time? I mean, most people have to tune their bass every so often, some every time they play - if you play hard, sometimes a couple times per song set, even! If your strings just won't stay in tune, it's possible they're not even the issue. But the easiest way to test is to try new strings and let them get settled in.

xChainge [https://xchainge.io ], a platform with a simple user interface for anonymous and decentralized exchange of assets based on the Ethereum blockchain, offers an alternative to centralized crypto asset exchanges with neither commission fees, nor mediator companies or KYC/AML. All of the platform's functionality is available in the xChainge Wallet application. The xChainge Wallet enables P2P transactions of crypto assets from an interface similar to popular online banking applications. xChainge Wallet for Windows will be launched in Q1 2018, followed by iOS and Android apps in Q2 2018.

Key features of the xChainge Wallet app include:

- Secure storage of crypto assets;

- Secure peer-to-peer exchanges;

- Easy-to-use smart contract builder for fully customizable exchange transactions;

- Smart dispute resolution with the help of mediators;

- Creating custom marketplaces.

The xChainge Wallet does not require verification and gives users full control over their assets. As a means of payment on the platform xChainge Token (XCT) is introduced.

The xChainge token is an ERC-20 Ethereum-based utility token, which is used on the platform to pay for Matcher node services and make Matcher node security deposits. It is issued by a non-profit fund which is creating the xChainge platform.

xChainge was co-founded by Albert Ibragimov, Danil Popov, Artur Ustimov and Egor Klimenko. All co-founders have a unique expertise in private equity, venture investment, financial products and marketing solutions. The core team of founders and early investors are the shareholders of Aktivo, a leading service of collective investments to commercial real estate property.

The crowdsale is scheduled to run between December 5th and December 30th, 2017. The team chose the Dutch auction model, similar to Raiden Network. At the start of the crowdsale each token will cost 0.05 ETH and the price will gradually decrease over time with constant rate. The auction hard cap is equal to 20 000 000 XCT tokens.

Source: xChainge
